					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632814#post-2168645</guid>
				<title>Re: Image Removal</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632814/scp-1522#post-2168645</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 29 Nov 2014 16:41:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Alex Ong</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1774309</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Aw&#8230; that image is what really made this SCP&#8230;</p> <p>Well&#8230; I do know the picture is actually one of a pair of the many abandoned ships in the Nouadhibou ship graveyard; I have seen other pictures of it before, some with the ship on the left in better condition and some with it in much worse. Perhaps if there's a way to find one of them and contact their authors&#8230;</p> <p>Edit: here's another picture of that same pair of ships I found: <a href="http://www.bloosee.com/infopoints/mauritania/dakhlet-nouadhibou/the-bay-of-nouadhibou-ship-graveyard/media/3706/">http://www.bloosee.com/infopoints/mauritania/dakhlet-nouadhibou/the-bay-of-nouadhibou-ship-graveyard/media/3706/</a><br /> There's a link to the author's profile on that site on the bottom of the picture.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632814#post-2164106</guid>
				<title>Image Removal</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632814/scp-1522#post-2164106</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 22 Nov 2014 22:06:26 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Heartful</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1932258</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>SCP-1522's image was removed because we could not properly determine whether or not the image was properly licensed or attributed. It may be added once again if/when proper attribution or proper use under CC guidelines is confirmed. Please contact Live2Die or another member of the Image Team if you have questions.</p> 
				 	]]>
